# .COPY tag problem - set Cloak of Absolute Silence as belonging to foo domain. unless some punk goes and makes a foo domain,
#	this should simply override any DOMAIN entries that silence might have...
#	not that silence is any domain spell, the point is using the copy tag to avoid having to read thru srd .lst files,
#	and thus greatly increasing efficiency of this .lst monkey

# bigger .COPY tag problem - not working in spells as of this alpha build I'm using :'(

# still not working as of post 5.5.2 alpha build - redoing spells w/o COPY tag

# rsrd .lsts seem to use COST tag for Material component and Focus costs -- shouldn't these be handled differently? (wand requires focus cost once, material 50 times?)

